<BaseLayout title="Terms of Use | CourtScope"><section class="hero"><div class="prose-width"><p class="eyebrow">Public policy</p><h1>Terms of Use</h1><p class="lede">Use CourtScope as civic information, not as a substitute for legal advice or official records.</p></div></section><section class="section"><div class="prose-width"><div class="card"><p>You may not use the site or datasets for harassment, doxxing, discrimination, voter suppression, unlawful profiling, automated legal decisions, judicial targeting, or unauthorized resale. Dataset-specific terms control reuse.</p><h2>Submission authority</h2><p>By uploading city data, you represent that you are authorized to provide the package for CourtScope review, that the declared scope and known gaps are described accurately, and that the automated repository-ready package contains no prohibited direct identifiers. Uploading a file does not guarantee acceptance, publication, scoring, or continued retention.</p><h2>What controls</h2><p>Official source terms, applicable law, dataset-specific notices, and the current published CourtScope methodology control where they are more specific. Contact <a href="mailto:info@courtscope.org">info@courtscope.org</a> for questions.</p><p><strong>Last updated:</strong> July 13, 2026</p></div></div></section></BaseLayout>